configDefinitions.description: Name of the columns to apply the function to. You can use a Java regular expression to apply the function to several columns.

configDefinitions.name: functionType
configDefinitions.label: Function Type
configDefinitions.description: Type of function to apply to matching columns. See the Snowflake documentation for details about listed functions.

labels: ADD_MONTHS - adds or subtracts number of months
AGE - calculates the difference between the specified date and the input value, in years
CONVERT_TIMEZONE - converts input to specified timezone
DATEADD - adds specified value to date or time expression
DATEDIFF - calculates difference between two inputs based on selected part
DAYNAME - extracts three-letter day of week from specified input
DAYOFMONTH - extracts the day of month
LAST_DAY - returns last day of month
NEXT_DAY - returns date for next e.g. Thursday if input date is Thursday
PREVIOUS_DAY - returns date for last e.g. Thursday if input date is Thursday
TO_DATE - converts input to date in specified format
TO_TIMESTAMP - converts input to timestamp in specified format

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.makeLit
configDefinitions.label: Treat as Constant
configDefinitions.description: When unchecked, takes specified value as a field name to use in the calculation. When checked, treats specified value as a literal constant.

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.numMonths
configDefinitions.label: Number of Months
configDefinitions.description: Number of months to add to the input field

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.targetTimezone
configDefinitions.label: Target Timezone
configDefinitions.description: Target timezone. Snowflake supports standard iana.org time zones. See Snowflake docs on CONVERT_TIMEZONE for more details.

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.sourceTimezone
configDefinitions.label: Source Timezone
configDefinitions.description: Source timezone. Required when input field is TIMESTAMP_NTZ. If not specified, the input timestamp field must have a timezone.

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.dateTimeParts
configDefinitions.label: Date Format
configDefinitions.description: Date or Time part used to extract field

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.value
configDefinitions.label: Value
configDefinitions.description: Number of units of time to add, e.g. to add two days, put 2

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.comparisonDate
configDefinitions.label: Comparison Date
configDefinitions.description: A valid date expression used to calculate date in the chosen function

configDefinitions.name: dateConf.dateFormat
configDefinitions.label: Format
configDefinitions.description: Format to be used for date or timestamp conversion. If not specified, Snowflake automatically detects format to use. See Snowflake docs on Date and Time Formats in Conversion Functions.

labels: ASCII - returns ASCII code of first character of string
CHAR - converts a Unicode code point into character matching input Unicode
CHARINDEX - searches for the first occurrence of a string and returns its position
CONTAINS - returns true if input contains value
ENDSWITH - returns true if input ends with value
INITCAP - returns first letter of each word in upper case
INSERT - replace substring of specified length with new string
LEFT - returns left most substring of input
LENGTH - returns length of input string or binary array
LOWER - returns input string in lower case
LPAD - left-pads string with characters from another string
MD5 - returns MD5 message digest of input
REGEXP_COUNT - counts number of times pattern occurs
REGEXP_REPLACE - replaces all occurrences of the specified pattern with another string
REMOVE - removes all occurrences of a specified substring
REPLACE - replaces all occurrences of a specified substring with another string
RIGHT - returns right most substring of input
RPAD - right-pads string with characters from another string
SHA1 - returns 40-character hex-encoded string containing SHA-1 digest
SHA2 - returns hex-encoded string containing N-bit SHA-2 digest
SOUNDEX - returns phonetic representation of input string
SPLIT - splits string with separator into array
STARTSWITH - returns true if input starts with value
TRIM - removes leading and trailing characters from string
UPPER - returns input string in upper case

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.makeLit
configDefinitions.label: Treat as Constant
configDefinitions.description: When unchecked, takes specified values as a field name to use in the calculation. When checked, treats specified values as a literal constant.

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.charIndexPosition
configDefinitions.label: Position
configDefinitions.description: Position (1-based) of string to begin searching for character index

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.pad
configDefinitions.label: Pad
configDefinitions.description: Pad to add to the string

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.trim
configDefinitions.label: Trim String
configDefinitions.description: If specified, trims string from beginning of input. Otherwise, trims blank spaces.

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.regexPosition
configDefinitions.label: Position
configDefinitions.description: Number of characters from beginning of string where function starts searching. Default is 1.

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.regexParameters
configDefinitions.label: Regex Parameters
configDefinitions.description: Determines the way matching occurs in regex. Can be a string made up of c, i, m, e, and s. See Snowflake docs on Parameters in Regular Expression functions for more details.

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.messageBits
configDefinitions.label: Message Bits
configDefinitions.description: Specified output digest size of SHA-2 hash

configDefinitions.name: stringConf.occurrence
configDefinitions.label: Occurrence
configDefinitions.description: Specifies which occurrence of the pattern to replace. Use 0 to replace all occurrences. Default is 0.

labels: ABS - returns absolute value of numeric expression
ATAN2 - computes inverse tangent of two arguments
CEIL - rounds input to nearest equal or larger integer
DIV0 - performs division but returns 0 when divisor is 0
EXP - computes Euler's number e raised to input
FLOOR - returns input rounded to nearest equal or smaller integer
LOG - returns logarithm of numeric expression
POW - returns number raised to specified power
ROUND - returns rounded values to specified scale
SQRT - computes square-root of non-negative numeric expression
TAN - computes tangent of value in radians
TRUNCATE - rounds down to nearest value with specified decimal places

configDefinitions.name: numericConf.divisor
configDefinitions.label: Divisor

configDefinitions.name: numericConf.base

configDefinitions.description: Base of the logarithm to be calculated from input field

configDefinitions.name: numericConf.power

configDefinitions.description: Raises input to the specified power

configDefinitions.name: numericConf.scale
configDefinitions.label: Scale
configDefinitions.description: Number of digits the output should include after the decimal point. If not specified, all digits after the decimal point are removed.

configDefinitions.name: conf.activeFlagType
configDefinitions.label: Active Column Type
configDefinitions.description: Define label to use for active vs. inactive columns

configDefinitions.name: conf.customInactiveColumn
configDefinitions.label: Label for Inactive Values
configDefinitions.description: Custom label to use for inactive values

configDefinitions.name: conf.startTimeColumn
configDefinitions.label: Start Timestamp Column
configDefinitions.description: Column to use as the start time for calculating the dimension value

configDefinitions.name: conf.useTimestampColumn
configDefinitions.label: Specify Timestamp Columns
configDefinitions.description: Enables specifying start and end time columns for rows

configDefinitions.name: conf.calculatedTimeColumn
configDefinitions.label: Calculated Timestamp Column
configDefinitions.description: Column to use for the end timestamp for old rows and start timestamp for new rows. NOTE: This column is removed from the data once the timestamp value is used.

configDefinitions.name: conf.specifyTimeCalc
configDefinitions.label: Specify Column for New Timestamps
configDefinitions.description: Enables specifying a column in the row for the end timestamp for old rows and start timestamp for new rows. Otherwise, the pipeline run timestamp is used.

configDefinitions.name: conf.scdType
configDefinitions.label: SCD Type
configDefinitions.description: Slowly changing dimension type to use

configDefinitions.name: conf.useVersionColumn
configDefinitions.label: Specify Version Column
configDefinitions.description: Use to specify a column in the input data that tracks the row's version

configDefinitions.name: conf.customActiveColumn
configDefinitions.label: Label for Active Values
configDefinitions.description: Custom label to use for active values

configDefinitions.name: conf.endTimeColumn
configDefinitions.label: End Timestamp Column
configDefinitions.description: Column to use as the end time for calculating the dimension value

configDefinitions.name: conf.useActiveColumn
configDefinitions.label: Specify Active Flag
configDefinitions.description: Use to specify a column in the input data that flags active rows

configDefinitions.name: conf.activeColumn
configDefinitions.label: Active Flag Column
configDefinitions.description: Column to track as the active flag

configDefinitions.name: conf.naturalKeyColumns
configDefinitions.label: Key Columns
configDefinitions.description: Natural key columns, used to join change data to master

configDefinitions.name: conf.newValuesBehavior
configDefinitions.label: Behavior for New Columns

labels: Keep for newest rows and set to null for previous rows

configDefinitions.description: Determines how to handle change data columns that do not exist in the master data

configDefinitions.name: conf.versionColumn
configDefinitions.label: Version Column
configDefinitions.description: Column to track as the version column. Must be an integer column in Snowflake.

configDefinitions.name: conf.createTable
configDefinitions.label: Create Table
configDefinitions.description: Creates a table when the specified table does not exist

configDefinitions.name: conf.dataDriftEnabled
configDefinitions.label: Data Drift Enabled
configDefinitions.description: Creates new columns in the target table if they do not exist. Also creates new columns with null values in the source tables as needed, to match the target table.

configDefinitions.name: conf.schema
configDefinitions.label: Schema
configDefinitions.description: Schema to write to

configDefinitions.name: conf.mergeKeys
configDefinitions.label: Merge Keys
configDefinitions.description: Keys to match when crafting join condition. Must be unique in the source.

configDefinitions.name: conf.overwriteMode
configDefinitions.label: Overwrite Mode
configDefinitions.description: Determines whether to drop or truncate the table when overwriting, if the table exists. If it does not exist, the behavior is governed by the Create Table option.

configDefinitions.name: conf.database
configDefinitions.label: Database
configDefinitions.description: Database to write to

configDefinitions.name: conf.table
configDefinitions.label: Table
configDefinitions.description: Table to write to

configDefinitions.name: conf.autoCalculateMerge
configDefinitions.label: Autocalculate Merge Operation
configDefinitions.description: When checked, uses __SS_META_KEYS and __SS_META_OPERATION columns generated during execution to calculate merge conditions. Uses 1 for insert, 2 for update, and 3 for delete. Throws exception if either column does not exist in the data set.

configDefinitions.name: conf.writeMode
configDefinitions.label: Write Mode

labels: Merge Rows in Table by Condition
Propagate updates from Slowly-Changing Dimension processor

configDefinitions.description: Defines how to write data to the specified table

configDefinitions.name: priorityBean.priority
configDefinitions.label: Priority
configDefinitions.description: If the order execution of a destination is important, you can use the priority field to specify how important each destination is.  Destinations with lower values are executed before those with higher values; and those with the same value are executed together.

configDefinitions.name: conf.newColsBehavior
configDefinitions.label: Behavior for New Columns
configDefinitions.description: Action to take when the pipeline includes columns that do not exist in the target table. Not used when creating the table.

configDefinitions.name: conf.mergeConfigs
configDefinitions.label: Merge Configuration

configDefinitions.name: whenClause
configDefinitions.label: When Clause
configDefinitions.description: Part of MERGE statement to configure.

configDefinitions.name: matchOperation
configDefinitions.label: Match Operation
configDefinitions.description: Determines whether to update or delete matched rows.

configDefinitions.name: matchCondition
configDefinitions.label: Additional Matched Condition
configDefinitions.description: Optional condition used in conjunction with merge condition. Use SQL WHERE clause syntax (e.g. myfield = 'foo'). By default, applies predicate to the source data set. Prefix the predicate with the target table name to apply the predicate to the target (e.g. 'targetTable.myfield = foo').

configDefinitions.name: notMatchedOperation
configDefinitions.label: Not Matched Operation
configDefinitions.description: Determines whether to insert or ignore unmatched rows.

configDefinitions.name: notMatchedCondition
configDefinitions.label: Additional Not Matched Condition
configDefinitions.description: Optional condition used in conjuction with merge condition. Use SQL WHERE clause syntax (e.g. myfield = 'foo'). By default, applies predicate to the source data set. This predicate can only be applied to the source data set.
Determines conditions for how to set the merge conditions. Adding a WHEN MATCHED clause does not automatically include a WHEN NOT MATCHED clause. Configure each clause separately.
